---
title: Beautiful Tables in Typst
description: |
  You can use HTML Tables with CSS stying in Typst via Quarto.
author: Gordon Woodhull
date: "07/01/2024"
image: https://placehold.co/1200x630
image-alt: "typst snapshot tk"
---



Quarto now allows HTML Tables with CSS styling to be output in Typst.

It does this by translating CSS properties into Typst properties. You can read about the feature [in the Guide](/docs/output-formats/typst.qmd#typst-css).[technical details [in the Advanced Docs](/docs/advanced/typst/typst-css.qmd)]{.aside}

Let's examine a few beautiful, expressive HTML tables that also look great in Typst! 

In all examples, the snapshot on the left is Typst, and the HTML version is on the right.

Here is a confusion matrix drawn with Pandas in Python. 

:::: {.column-body-outset}
::: {layout-ncol=2}
![](images/pandas-confusion-matrix.png)



